						               													<description>Join the race against time in Clockwise, the worker placement board game played on functioning mechanical gears.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Based on a Jules Verne short story, players collect resources and build clocks to save the city of Geneva. The game board consists of five inner mechanical gears and one large outer gear that rotates all the inner gears when it is moved. The inner gears contain resource spots that correspond to resource items used to build clocks. Players must place one of their workers on the starting position of any gear. The more turns you wait on the inner gears, the more valuable resources you will receive.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With the resources claimed, players can trade them in to build one of the revealed clocks located at the bottom of the board. Each clock has unique resources to build them and each hold a different victory point value when completing them. The game is played for 24 hours and when the clock strikes midnight, the game is over and clock victory points are tallied. The player with the most victory points wins the game and is titled as Geneva's next Clockmaster. Can you restore order before time runs out?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
